author: Stephen Price
title: Skygazers treated to Northern Lights show across Wales ‚Äì with more to come
text:
Northern Lights at Llyn y Fan Fach. Image: Cormac Downes Skygazers across Wales have been treated to a stunning show of the Northern Lights ‚Äì with experts saying there is still more to come.
The sun has now entered its period of greatest activity, which means we could be seeing more colourful displays of the aurora borealis until the middle of next year.
Hope you enjoy these timelapses showing last nights EPIC northern lights display over Wales. Did you see it?
üìå Mwnt, Llangrannog, Dryslwyn Castle #astrophotography #aurora #auroraborealis #northernlights @TamithaSkov @TweetAurora @Luminar_Neo @BBCWalesNews @ProfBrianCox pic.twitter.com/aHa58H9t8e
‚Äî Mathew Browne (@mathewbrowne) October 11, 2024
Our home star typically follows an 11-year-cycle, with periods of intense activity followed by a quiet phase.
Collision
During its active bursts, also known as solar maximum, the sun releases charged particles that travel through space at speeds of around one million miles per hour.
Goleuni‚Äôr Gogledd Y Fenni / Northern Lights, Abergavenny. Image: Steve Price Some of the particles are captured by the Earth‚Äôs magnetic field and collide with oxygen and nitrogen atoms and molecules in the atmosphere.
Northern Lights in Wales last night, unbelievable. pic.twitter.com/qTyKuPJAVC
‚Äî Lis üëª (@lisajt_x) October 11, 2024
These atoms and molecules then shed the energy they gained from the collision, emitting light at various wavelengths to create colourful displays in the night sky.
According to Nasa, oxygen emits either a greenish-yellow light ‚Äì which is the most familiar colour of the aurora ‚Äì or a red light, while nitrogen generally gives off a blue light.
Northern Lights, Wales @metoffice pic.twitter.com/slVVd1qv27
‚Äî kate (@katecicely) October 10, 2024
The oxygen and nitrogen molecules also emit ultraviolet light, which can only be detected by special cameras on satellites.
Phenomena
Photos of the dazzling natural phenomenon were captured across Wales last night, with the glorious sight being witnessed across the entire country.
The current peak is expected to until mid-2025, according to the Royal Astronomical Society.
Just after 10pm, the Northern Lights put on an even better show. The Berwyn‚Äôs, North Wales. #Aurore #Auroraborealis #northernlights pic.twitter.com/y5F5LqT0OR
‚Äî Richard Bowler (@RichardBowler1) October 11, 2024
After that, aurora displays will only be visible in high latitude countries such as Alaska, Canada, Iceland, Scandinavia, Finland and Russia.
The southern lights, or aurora australis, can be observed in Antarctica, New Zealand and Australia.

author: NewsBreak Original
title: Valley Allstars lose Game 1 in World Series to good Team Georgia; look to start fresh against Tennessee
text:
By Annie Bresee ,
6 hours ago The Valley 10U AAA Allstars, also known as Team Alabama, made their debut at the Diamond Youth Baseball World Series on Thursday morning.
However, the team fell to their opponent, Team Georgia, from Schley County, 10-3. The first game of the tournament is ‚Äúpool play,‚Äù meaning their journey is not over. The boys will now play Team Tennessee tomorrow at 11 a.m.
Valley‚Äôs starter Benton Earl had a solid day pitching 2 ‚Öì innings with three hits. However, a walk for the first batter followed by a single and an inside-the-park home run got Schley County an early 3-0 lead.
The Allstars were able to shut down Team Georgia for two innings. However, in the fourth Schley tacked on three more runs with a single, another inside-the-park home run and an error. In the fifth, with two outs, the Georgia team singles with a man on second to make it 7-0 and walks another in for another run.
With some rain in Bossier, came some light for the Valley team. In the bottom of the fifth, Valley played small ball allowing for Noah Lynd to score on a bases-loaded walk from Baylor Anglin.
However, Schley seemingly halted the momentum, scoring another two runs on two outs in the top of the sixth. In the last half inning Valley would not be able to come all the way back.
But, Team Alabama didn‚Äôt go down without a fight. Earl doubled as the first batter. A single by Cole Carswell and an error by Schley‚Äôs shortstop get Benton home and Carswell to second. Speedster Carwell was moved over by a sacrifice fly from Mason Landrum. Finally, Ingram S brought Cole to the dish with a groundout, for a final score of 10-3.
The team‚Äôs Facebook page, 2024 Valley 10U All-Stars, is livestreaming the games. If they lose tomorrow the team will be sent to a separate bracket and will have a harder trek to the championship. However, with a win, tomorrow would get Valley a bye to the next round.

author: dsingson
title: Wembanyama: Blood clot to end Spurs star's NBA season
text:
BASKETBALL Wembanyama: Blood clot appears to end Spurs star‚Äôs NBA season By: Agence France Presse February 21,2025 - 06:21 AM
The San Antonio Spurs announced on February 20, 2025, that the team‚Äôs French forward-center #01 Victor Wembanyama has been diagnosed with deep vein thrombosis in his right shoulder and he will miss the remainder of the 2024-2025 NBA season. Photo is Wembanyama during a press conference after a training sesssion in Paris on January 22, 2025.
HOUSTON, United States ‚Äî San Antonio Spurs star Victor Wembanyama is expected to miss the rest of the NBA season after being diagnosed with deep vein thrombosis in his right shoulder, the team said Thursday.
The Spurs said in a statement that the 21-year-old French player was diagnosed with the blood clot after he returned to San Antonio following last Sunday‚Äôs All-Star game in San Francisco.
‚ÄúWembanyama is expected to miss the remainder of the 2024-25 regular season,‚Äù the Spurs said. ‚ÄúThe team will provide updates as appropriate.‚Äù
READ:
NBA: LeBron James says he won‚Äôt play in All-Star game
NBA: Nikola Jokic turns 30 and averaging a triple-double this season
NBA All-Star: Wembanyama, Chris Paul DQ‚Äôed after plan backfires
The announcement brings a premature end to another outstanding campaign by Wembanyama, who earned Rookie of the Year honors last season after being taken first overall in the NBA draft.
‚ÄúIt‚Äôs tough,‚Äù San Antonio‚Äôs veteran point guard Chris Paul said of losing Wembanyama, who was averaging 24.3 points, 11.0 rebounds, 3.7 assists and a league-best 3.8 blocks in 46 games for the Spurs this season.
‚ÄúTough more than anything, I think for all of us, knowing how much he means to our team, but more so knowing how much he means to the game and how much he loves to play.‚Äù
Other NBA players have dealt with similar health concerns. Chris Bosh, a two-time NBA champion with the Miami heat, was ultimately forced to retire at the age of 32 after repeatedly dealing with blood clots.
But the Detroit Pistons‚Äô Ausar Thompson has returned to play 33 games this season afer he was diagnosed with a blood clot in March of last year. Brandon Ingram, now with the Toronto Raptors, recovered after being diagnosed with a blood clot in his right arm in 2019.
But it‚Äôs a big blow for a player who made an immediate impact on arriving in the league and whose influence is only growing in his second season.
The 7-foot-3 (2.21m) Wembanyama became an All-Star for the first time when he was chosen as a reserve.
Young Minnesota star Anthony Edwards noted Wembanyama‚Äôs rise during All-Star weekend when he was asked if he considered himself a candidate for ‚Äúnext face of the league‚Äù.
‚ÄúNot really,‚Äù Edwards said, ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs what they‚Äôve got Wemby for.‚Äù
The Spurs have reportedly indicated they expect Wembanyama to make a full recovery.
While the team‚Äôs announcement didn‚Äôt rule out the possibility that Wembanyama could be fit for the playoffs, the chances of San Antonio reaching the post-season without him look slim.
The Spurs are in 12th place in the Western Conference, two spots away from the final play-in berth now held by the Golden State Warriors.
Even with the arrival of high-scoring guard De‚ÄôAaron Fox from Sacramento at the trade deadline, the Spurs will likely suffer without their centerpiece.
‚ÄòCan‚Äôt replace Vic‚Äô ‚ÄúI think everybody understands that basketball is what we do and not who we are,‚Äù Paul told reporters at San Antonio‚Äôs practice session ahead of Thursday‚Äôs game against Phoenix.
‚ÄúSo life and everything is so much more important. But for us, we know losing a big part of our team like that is (compensated for) by committee.‚Äù
‚ÄúTrust me, you can‚Äôt replace Vic,‚Äù Paul said. ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt stand on a guy‚Äôs shoulders and block every shot that comes to the rim.
‚ÄúAside from his basketball ability, his charisma and what he brings into the locker room I think is what we‚Äôll miss the most.‚Äù
Wembanyama was playing in the French league a year and a half ago before his selection as the number one pick in the 2023 NBA draft set him on the path to global stardom.
He helped France capture the silver medal at last year‚Äôs Paris Olympics, where they fell to the United States in the final.
His sophomore season included a trip home to France, where the Spurs split two games in Paris with the Indiana Pacers.
On course for potential defensive player of the year honors, Wembanyama will now not play enough games to be eligible for any of the major end of season awards.
Losing Wembanyama is another blow for the Spurs, after legendary longtime coach Gregg Popovich suffered a stroke in November that forced him to take indefinite leave from the team.
Paul insisted that the Spurs remained focused on making the post-season.
‚ÄúThat‚Äôs the plan,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs absolutely the plan. I know Vic, I know Pop, they wouldn‚Äôt have it any other way.‚Äù

author: Gary Dixon (g_dixon)
title: Iran releases crew of seized MSC and Zodiac-linked container ship in ‚Äòhumanitarian act‚Äô | TradeWinds
text: Iran has freed the crew of the MSC Mediterranean Shipping Company-managed container ship that it hijacked last month. Foreign minister Hossein Amir-Abdollahian said the captain and the remaining 23 other seafarers would be allowed to leave the country. But the 15,000-teu, Portugal-flagged MSC Aries (built 2020) will remain under Iran‚Äôs control, he added, according to Reuters. The vessel was seized on 13 April in apparent retaliation for Israel‚Äôs bombing of Iran‚Äôs embassy complex in Syria. An Indian cadet was allowed to fly home in April. The crew consists of 17 other Indians, four Filipinos and others from Estonia, Pakistan and Russia. ‚ÄúThe seized ship, which turned off its radar in Iran‚Äôs territorial waters and jeopardised the security of navigation, is under judicial detention,‚Äù Amir-Abdollahian said, according to a foreign ministry post on X late on Thursday night. The minister described the crew release as a humanitarian act. MSC is also the operator and charterer of the MSC Aries, which is owned by an affiliate of UK-based Zodiac Maritime, owned by Israeli tycoon Eyal Ofer, who is based in Monaco. At the end of April, after receiving criticism from the International Maritime Organization over the hijacking, Tehran indicated that the crew could be allowed out of the country soon. ‚ÄòSerious concern‚Äô ‚ÄúThe humanitarian issue of the release of the ship‚Äôs crew is of serious concern to us,‚Äù Amir-Abdollahian told his Portuguese counterpart, Paulo Rangel, during a telephone conversation at the time. The 24 seafarers were all in good health, had received consular access and their ambassadors had been ‚Äúinformed of their release and extradition‚Äù, Amir-Abdollahian was quoted as saying. MSC has not commented. Portugal defended the ship‚Äôs master, notifying Iranian authorities that he had a right to switch off its AIS. Speaking at the IMO last month, Iran‚Äôs representative described the seizure of the MSC Aries as a ‚Äútechnical issue‚Äù and said crew would be repatriated based on ‚Äúminimum safe manning standards‚Äù.

author: Svyatenko Tamara
title: Ukraine will be between the anticyclone Ernst and the recent cyclone Didenko said when strong frosts will hit
text:
Ukraine will be between the anticyclone Ernst and the recent cyclone: Didenko said when strong frosts will hit.
Weather on Friday, December 13
Forecaster Natalia Didenko reported that dry weather with sunny clearings is expected in Ukraine on Friday, December 13. However, light snow is possible at night in the north and during the day in the east. Ukraine will be between the anticyclone and the recent cyclone, so gusty winds are expected.
Cold weather continues, with temperatures at night ranging from -2 to -7 and during the day from -1 to -6 degrees. Be cautious on the roads due to ice, choose sturdy and non-slip shoes, and do not move too quickly.
Weather in Kyiv
In Kyiv, no precipitation is expected on Friday, but with strong northwestern winds and frost. The temperature will range from -3 to -6 degrees. It is recommended to dress in layers and warmly. Warming will begin on Sunday.
Recall that an atmospheric front will cover Ukraine.
